PFFT --- Pretty Fast Fourier Transform
======================================

PFFT is a library for performing FFTs on GPUs using OpenCL. It was inspired by FFTW (www.fftw.org) and attempts to match the FFTW interface.


FAQ
---

Q. What licence does PFFT use?
A. PFFT is released under the MIT Licence.

Q. Do I need to acknowledge this project in my own work?
A. No, this is not a requirement of the licence. It would however be greatly appreciated by the author, so it is left to your better judgement.

Q. How is the name pronounced?
A. A sharp exhalation through loosely closed lips, as when demonstrating indignation at the remarks of another.


